Observations¶

  • New type of loan, Consumer Loan, which was not there in Application data frame. 43% of loans are consumer loans. 44% cash loans and rest revolving/XNA
  • Approved loans are 62% and refused, cancelled, unused - rest
  • 73% are repeaters.
  • 41% of the applicants have taken loan for POS purchase.
  • Name seller industry has 51% XNA values, Consumer electronics is next highest category at 23%
In [37]:
#  Continous data
a = 8  # number of rows
b = 3  # number of columns
c = 1  # initialize plot counter

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(15,12))

for i in p_app.columns:
    if p_app[i].dtypes=="float64" or p_app[i].dtypes=="float32" :
        plt.subplot(a, b, c)
        plt.title('{}, subplot: {}{}{}'.format(i, a, b, c))
        plt.xlabel(i)
        sns.boxplot(p_app[i])
        c = c + 1

fig.tight_layout()
plt.show();

prior_corr= unapprov_data.drop(axis=1,columns=['SK_ID_CURR','SK_ID_PREV'] )

correlation=prior_corr.corr().abs()
####
corr_pre = correlation.where(np.triu(np.ones(correlation.shape),k=1).astype(np.bool)).unstack().reset_index()
corr_pre.columns=['Column1','Column2','Correlation']
corr_pre.dropna(subset=['Correlation'],inplace=True)
corr_pre = corr_pre.sort_values(by=['Correlation'], ascending=False)
